From f940956b8075bcb4281563f5cef578da05800228 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 22:42:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 16/17] task4: wire the LLM consolidator into the publication
 pass

_effective_gate_llm_call resolves the injection seam first, then a
functools.partial over default_llm_call when publication_gate and
gate_consolidator_model are both set, else None (byte-identical
pre-change path). _do_publication_pass consolidates after grouping and
re-runs verify/stamp/group from disk when something was published, so
the consolidated note is stamped through the multi-attempt path and
archived originals drop out of the served views within the same pass.

Six manager-level integration scenarios green (happy path, hallucinated
score, LLM error, re-consolidation, settle, flag-off). Full suite 753
passed, 73 gate tests unmodified, ruff clean. Reviewed, approved.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
